<br>
Let me give you just a slight example of our small community here in Gaeta, Italy.<br>
<br>
When I arrived here in 1998, Italy was still using the Lire.<br>
<br>
1 US$ = 1600 Lire (appx) when I arrived<br>
Shortly there after (Clinton still in White House)<br>
1US$ = 2200 Lire which was great.  Our housing costs dropped (if you payed 900,000 Lire for a house per month, your rent just dropped appx 30 percent)<br>
<br>
